♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING
OVER STEREO) ♪

16:08.426 --> 16:11.093
<i>Who’s there? I’ve got a gun!</i>

16:11.093 --> 16:13.830
<i>I just can’t find it right now!</i>

16:15.934 --> 16:17.099
<i>Who sent you?</i>

16:17.099 --> 16:19.102
<i>I won that
Battle of the Network Stars</i>

16:19.102 --> 16:20.502
<i>fair and square!</i>

16:20.502 --> 16:25.541
I j... I just saw you on television.

16:25.541 --> 16:30.346
See, I recognized you
as Mr. Butlertron model 8133B.

16:30.346 --> 16:32.081
I was sure they’d all
been destroyed

16:32.081 --> 16:33.583
during the Ford Administration.

16:33.583 --> 16:35.384
And yet, here you are.

16:35.384 --> 16:40.956
<i>And yet, here I am.
Now, get out of my face-plate.</i>

16:40.956 --> 16:44.194
Please. I’m desperately
in need of your services.

16:46.428 --> 16:49.130
<i>You want me to work for you?</i>

16:49.130 --> 16:52.135
<i>What could you possibly offer me
that I haven’t already got?</i>

16:52.135 --> 16:56.473
<i>I’m a multi-camera situation
comedy star.</i>

16:57.907 --> 17:00.877
I can offer to make you
a part of this.

17:00.877 --> 17:02.244
♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:07.786 --> 17:10.686
<i>A family.</i>

17:10.686 --> 17:13.589
No! They’re baby clones
of historical figures

17:13.589 --> 17:15.827
so I can start
a clone theme park.

17:16.527 --> 17:19.996
<i>Wait. You can clone people?</i>

17:19.996 --> 17:21.264
Of course, I can!

17:21.264 --> 17:23.766
<i>Then I will give up
my fulfilling Hollywood life</i>

17:23.766 --> 17:25.168
<i>and come work for you.</i>

17:25.168 --> 17:27.969
<i>But, I need you to make me
a promise.</i>

17:27.969 --> 17:32.008
<i>You’ll clone one more person.</i>

17:32.008 --> 17:35.310
Your life has been
so epic and award-worthy.

17:35.310 --> 17:38.913
Meanwhile, I have no one.
I’m all alone.

17:38.913 --> 17:42.488
<i>There is still someone
you can always count on.</i>

17:42.888 --> 17:44.253
You, Mr. B?

17:44.253 --> 17:47.589
<i>What? No. You.</i>

17:47.589 --> 17:49.792
<i>Don’t put your trust
in other people.</i>

17:49.792 --> 17:50.993
<i>They’ll only let you down</i>

17:50.993 --> 17:53.399
<i>until eventually
you can’t take it anymore.</i>

17:58.403 --> 18:00.839
Hey. Don’t cry, Mr. B.

18:03.507 --> 18:07.346
Oh, never mind. It was Au Jus
from that prime rib sandwich.

18:10.379 --> 18:15.117
<i>Goodbye, Joan.</i>

18:15.117 --> 18:17.954
Goodbye, Mr. B.
Thanks for the advice.

18:17.954 --> 18:20.126
Hey, wait.
Your battery’s getting low.

18:22.694 --> 18:24.530
<i>I know.</i>

18:33.938 --> 18:37.539
Last Stop, Jumpers Cliff,
named for Bonnie Jean Jumper,

18:37.539 --> 18:40.576
who invented jumpers,
or as we call them today,

18:40.576 --> 18:42.414
rompers or one-pieces.

18:43.114 --> 18:45.148
Okay, end of the line.

18:58.563 --> 19:01.767
Oh, God, why is life so hard?

19:03.001 --> 19:04.333
Huh! I’m sorry.
Were you going to jump?

19:04.333 --> 19:05.869
I didn’t mean to cut in line.

19:05.869 --> 19:08.037
<i>I’m not here to jump.</i>

19:08.037 --> 19:10.339
<i>I’m here to stare
into the sunset</i>

19:10.339 --> 19:13.876
<i>and let my battery power down.</i>

19:13.876 --> 19:16.015
<i>Forever.</i>

19:16.949 --> 19:18.484
<i>But there is a line over there.</i>

19:19.451 --> 19:21.450
Oh. That’s a lot of people.

19:21.450 --> 19:23.819
That’ll take all day!
You know what? Forget it.

19:23.819 --> 19:26.492
Life’s too short,
you know what I mean?

19:36.101 --> 19:38.604
♪ (MELANCHOLIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

19:45.544 --> 19:47.779
<i>Wesley.</i>

19:51.414 --> 19:54.453
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

19:58.123 --> 19:59.989
You’re not going anywhere,

19:59.989 --> 20:01.193
Mr. B.

20:05.730 --> 20:07.133
I owe you an apology.

20:08.867 --> 20:10.233
You did try to tell me,

20:10.233 --> 20:13.101
but the note must have gotten
stuck on my shoe

20:13.101 --> 20:16.873
and I didn’t see it until I went
to change into my house clogs.

20:16.873 --> 20:18.841
What do you say, old pal?

20:18.841 --> 20:20.744
Will you forgive
an old turkey-lurkey

20:20.744 --> 20:22.612
and come on home?

20:22.612 --> 20:25.080
<i>- No.</i>
- Why not?

20:25.080 --> 20:27.250
<i>For the simple, epic
and award-worthy reason</i>

20:27.250 --> 20:29.919
<i>that I’m unable to trust
a single soul.</i>

20:29.919 --> 20:32.922
<i>Because I have no soul.</i>

20:32.922 --> 20:34.790
Don’t you realize?

20:34.790 --> 20:36.258
I’m a scientist!

20:36.258 --> 20:39.728
I don't have a soul!
The clones don't have souls!

20:39.728 --> 20:42.632
They’re just
horny science experiments!

20:42.632 --> 20:44.166
We’re all soulless.

20:44.166 --> 20:47.070
Together! And so is he.

20:47.070 --> 20:51.074
<i>Wesley!</i>

20:51.074 --> 20:53.875
I made you a promise
when you came to work with me.

20:53.875 --> 20:58.647
<i>But today you said you never
intended to keep your promise.</i>

20:58.647 --> 21:00.249
That’s because
I was too embarrassed

21:00.249 --> 21:01.517
to tell you the truth.

21:01.517 --> 21:03.219
Been trying to do this
for years,

21:03.219 --> 21:04.820
but I’m such a goofus!

21:04.820 --> 21:07.559
And I kept confusing my own
hair clumps with Wesley’s.

21:08.226 --> 21:09.658
I kept cloning myself!

21:09.658 --> 21:12.126
And then I had to murder
the clones of me.

21:12.126 --> 21:16.668
This was the last Wesley hair.
I did it! Your brother is alive.

21:19.738 --> 21:21.371
<i>This is the best day of my life!</i>

21:25.010 --> 21:26.512
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

21:28.046 --> 21:29.879
<i>No!</i>

21:31.514 --> 21:33.549
Help me, Mr. B!

21:33.549 --> 21:36.888
My delicate hands
can’t hold on much longer!

21:55.606 --> 21:58.373
I promise,
I’ll never leave your side.

21:58.373 --> 22:00.342
On Earth or in Heaven.

22:00.342 --> 22:02.940
And a promise
between brothers is...

22:02.940 --> 22:04.881
- Forever.
<i>- Forever.</i>

22:04.881 --> 22:06.449
Mr. B!
How dare you not tell me

22:06.449 --> 22:07.586
I have crab in my teeth?

22:19.862 --> 22:23.398
<i>Goodbye again, Wesley.</i>

22:23.398 --> 22:24.600
I was a little worried there

22:24.600 --> 22:26.869
when you flashed
on the crab memory.

22:26.869 --> 22:28.704
Why did you choose me?

22:28.704 --> 22:32.275
<i>I know that Wesley
will go to Heaven.</i>

22:32.275 --> 22:34.443
<i>But you and I don’t need to.</i>

22:34.443 --> 22:39.581
<i>Because, we’re already there.</i>

22:39.581 --> 22:42.752
Uh. Wha-- Uh.
I don't understand.

22:42.752 --> 22:44.820
<i>I love those clones.</i>

22:44.820 --> 22:48.591
<i>And I could never leave
what we built together.</i>

22:48.591 --> 22:51.360
We have created quite a family,
haven’t we?

22:51.360 --> 22:54.833
<i>Gasp! A family!</i>

22:56.467 --> 23:01.940
<i>It must be raining
because robots can’t cry.</i>

23:05.444 --> 23:07.513
<i>Or can they?</i>

23:08.346 --> 23:11.247
So, are you coming back
to the lab?

23:11.247 --> 23:13.850
<i>Of course, I am.
No way you can handle</i>

23:13.850 --> 23:15.117
<i>the final exciting chapter</i>

23:15.117 --> 23:18.485
<i>of "Operation Spread Eagle"
alone.</i>

23:21.326 --> 23:22.859
<i>Can you believe I cried?</i>

23:22.859 --> 23:24.961
You didn’t cry,
that was a malfunction.

23:24.961 --> 23:27.596
<i>- No, I totally cried.</i>
- Did not!

23:27.596 --> 23:30.599
<i>I did cry. It was salty.</i>

23:30.599 --> 23:32.168
<i>There’s no magic
in the world.</i>

23:32.168 --> 23:35.304
<i>Robots don’t cry.
Rainbows don’t exist.</i>

23:35.304 --> 23:36.839
<i>Rainbows do exist.</i>

23:36.839 --> 23:38.840
<i>Okay,
I’ll give you rainbows.</i>

23:38.840 --> 23:41.344
<i>I’m telling you,
they were real tears.</i>

23:41.344 --> 23:42.978
<i>Ah, you wish, robit.</i>

23:42.978 --> 23:45.014
<i>It was wet
in human style.</i>

23:45.014 --> 23:46.716
<i>Oh, you want
to see crying? Watch this.</i>

23:48.618 --> 23:50.319
<i>Ah, see? That was fake!</i>

23:50.319 --> 23:51.820
<i>So is your hair.</i>

23:51.820 --> 23:56.025
<i>Wow, whatever!
I like our repartee.</i>

23:56.025 --> 23:58.630
<i>Oh, yes.
It’s quite witty.</i>

23:59.865 --> 24:02.134
♪ (UPLIFTING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

24:20.886 --> 24:22.954
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
